title: Google\Cloud\DataCatalog\V1\SearchCatalogResult
name: SearchCatalogResult
description:
Result in the response to a search request.

Each result captures details of one entry that matches the search.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.datacatalog.v1.SearchCatalogResult

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.description: Constructor.

params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.search_result_type
params.description: Type of the search result. You can use this field to determine which get method to call to fetch the full resource.

params.name: data.search_result_subtype
params.description: Sub-type of the search result. A dot-delimited full type of the resource. The same type you specify in the type search predicate. Examples: entry.table, entry.dataStream, tagTemplate.

params.name: data.relative_resource_name
params.description: The relative name of the resource in URL format. Examples: projects/{PROJECT_ID}/locations/{LOCATION_ID}/entryGroups/{ENTRY_GROUP_ID}/entries/{ENTRY_ID} projects/{PROJECT_ID}/tagTemplates/{TAG_TEMPLATE_ID}

params.name: data.linked_resource
params.description: The full name of the Google Cloud resource the entry belongs to. For more information, see [Full Resource Name] (/apis/design/resource_names#full_resource_name). Example: //bigquery.googleapis.com/projects/PROJECT_ID/datasets/DATASET_ID/tables/TABLE_ID

params.name: data.modify_time
params.description: The last modification timestamp of the entry in the source system.

params.name: data.integrated_system
params.description: Output only. The source system that Data Catalog automatically integrates with, such as BigQuery, Cloud Pub/Sub, or Dataproc Metastore.

params.name: data.user_specified_system
params.description: Custom source system that you can manually integrate Data Catalog with.

params.name: data.fully_qualified_name
params.description: Fully qualified name (FQN) of the resource. FQNs take two forms: For non-regionalized resources: {SYSTEM}:{PROJECT}.{PATH_TO_RESOURCE_SEPARATED_WITH_DOTS} For regionalized resources: {SYSTEM}:{PROJECT}.{LOCATION_ID}.{PATH_TO_RESOURCE_SEPARATED_WITH_DOTS} Example for a DPMS table: dataproc_metastore:PROJECT_ID.LOCATION_ID.INSTANCE_ID.DATABASE_ID.TABLE_ID

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: The display name of the result.

params.name: data.description
params.description: Entry description that can consist of several sentences or paragraphs that describe entry contents.
